value.0: Charles Zarandt was the last Lord-Baron of Tejarn Gate. Considered in his prime, at a ripe young age of 38, he began to show signs of madness. The taxes were raised tenfold. The toll to enter and pass through the Tejarn Gate was set at 50 Aenar in spite of opposition from his fellow Lords. He was deposed by the Knights of Agis who now hold the Tejarn Gate open in the name of the Queen.
